        -: 1241:/* ----------------------------- regexp.h ----------------------------- */
        -: 1242:
        -: 1243:/* PVLVs need to act as a superset of all scalar types - they are basically
        -: 1244: * PVMGs with a few extra fields.
        -: 1245: * REGEXPs are first class scalars, but have many fields that can't be copied
        -: 1246: * into a PVLV body.
        -: 1247: *
        -: 1248: * Hence we take a different approach - instead of a copy, PVLVs store a pointer
        -: 1249: * back to the original body. To avoid increasing the size of PVLVs just for the
        -: 1250: * rare case of REGEXP assignment, this pointer is stored in the memory usually
        -: 1251: * used for SvLEN(). Hence the check for SVt_PVLV below, and the ? : ternary to
        -: 1252: * read the pointer from the two possible locations. The macro SvLEN() wraps the
        -: 1253: * access to the union's member xpvlenu_len, but there is no equivalent macro
        -: 1254: * for wrapping the union's member xpvlenu_rx, hence the direct reference here.
        -: 1255: *
        -: 1256: * See commit df6b4bd56551f2d3 for more details. */
        -: 1257:
