        -: 4996:
        -: 4997:/* copy a string to a safe spot */
        -: 4998:
        -: 4999:/*
        -: 5000:=for apidoc_section $string
        -: 5001:=for apidoc      savepv
        -: 5002:=for apidoc_item savepvn
        -: 5003:=for apidoc_item savepvs
        -: 5004:=for apidoc_item savesvpv
        -: 5005:=for apidoc_item savesharedpv
        -: 5006:=for apidoc_item savesharedpvn
        -: 5007:=for apidoc_item savesharedpvs
        -: 5008:=for apidoc_item savesharedsvpv
        -: 5009:
        -: 5010:These each return a pointer to a newly allocated string which is a duplicate of
        -: 5011:the one given by the input argument.  Effectively, they implement the C library
        -: 5012:L<C<strdup(3)>>.
        -: 5013:
        -: 5014:The forms differ in three main ways:
        -: 5015:
        -: 5016:=over
        -: 5017:
        -: 5018:=item 1.
        -: 5019:
        -: 5020:Whether or not the newly allocated memory is in an area that is sharable
        -: 5021:between threads (the forms with C<shared> in their names) or if it is in an
        -: 5022:area exclusive to the calling thread (the other forms).
        -: 5023:
        -: 5024:=item 2.
        -: 5025:
        -: 5026:How the string to be copied is specified.
        -: 5027:
        -: 5028:In the C<savepv> and C<savesharedpv> forms, the source string is a C language
        -: 5029:NUL-terminated string, or C<NULL>.  If C<NULL>, no allocation is done, and
        -: 5030:the functions return NULL.
        -: 5031:
        -: 5032:In the C<savepvn> and C<savesharedpvn> forms, C<pv> (if not NULL) points to the
        -: 5033:first byte of the string to duplicate, and an additional parameter, C<len>,
        -: 5034:specifies the number of bytes to copy.  Hence, C<pv> may contain embedded-NUL
        -: 5035:characters.  It is illegal for C<pv> to be NULL when calling C<savesharedpvn>
        -: 5036:(asserted against in DEBUGGING builds).  If it is NULL in C<savepvn>, C<len>
        -: 5037:bytes of zeroed memory are allocated.
        -: 5038:
        -: 5039:In the C<savepvs> and C<savesharedpvs> forms, the string must be a C literal
        -: 5040:string, enclosed in double quotes.
        -: 5041:
        -: 5042:In the C<savesvpv> and C<savesharedsvpv> forms, the string to duplicate is
