        -: 5045:=item 3.
        -: 5046:
        -: 5047:Memory deallocation
        -: 5048:
        -: 5049:To prevent memory leaks, the memory allocated for the new string needs to be
        -: 5050:freed when no longer needed.
        -: 5051:
        -: 5052:=over
        -: 5053:
        -: 5054:=item C<non-shared> forms
        -: 5055:
        -: 5056:Use the C<L</Safefree>> function, or L<C<SAVEFREEPV>|perlguts/SAVEFREEPV(p)>.
        -: 5057:However, BE AWARE, this can happen automatically on some platforms, such as
        -: 5058:Windows, when the thread that allocated it ends.  So if you need that not to
        -: 5059:happen, you need to use a C<shared> form.
        -: 5060:
        -: 5061:=item C<shared> forms
        -: 5062:
        -: 5063:Use the C<PerlMemShared_free> function.
        -: 5064:
        -: 5065:=back
        -: 5066:
        -: 5067:=back
