        -: 5189:unless C<size> is 0 or the original C<dst> string was longer than C<size> (in
        -: 5190:practice this should not happen as it means that either C<size> is incorrect or
        -: 5191:that C<dst> is not a proper C<NUL>-terminated string).
        -: 5192:
        -: 5193:Note that C<size> is the full size of the destination buffer and
        -: 5194:the result is guaranteed to be C<NUL>-terminated if there is room.  Note that
        -: 5195:room for the C<NUL> should be included in C<size>.
        -: 5196:
        -: 5197:The return value is the total length that C<dst> would have if C<size> is
        -: 5198:sufficiently large.  Thus it is the initial length of C<dst> plus the length of
        -: 5199:C<src>.  If C<size> is smaller than the return, the excess was not appended.
        -: 5200:
